EU Carbon Rebounds From Two-Month Low Amid Surging Volume

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-05-24T08:58:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/eu-carbon-rebounds-from-two-month-low-amid-surging-volume.html
European Union carbon permits
rebounded from a two-month low after volumes jumped yesterday.  EU allowances for December rose as much as 1.2 percent to
16.35 euros ($23) a metric ton on the ICE Futures Europe
exchange in  London  and traded at 16.29 euros at 9:30 a.m. local
time. They fell as low as 16.07 euros a ton yesterday, the
cheapest price since March 14.  Trading volume for the contract, the industry benchmark,
jumped 35 percent yesterday to 10.9 million tons, the most
trades in a single day since May 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  